Orji, who will be 73 years old in 2023, said he will resist pressures to seek positions that will keep him in active politics beyond 2023 when he completes his eight years in the senate. Senator Theodore Orji, the 70-year-old former Governor of Abia State has revealed that he would quit politics in 2023 to give way for the youths. At a wedding over the weekend, Orji, who will be 73 years old in 2023, said he will resist pressures to seek positions that will keep him in active politics beyond 2023 when he completes his eight years in the senate. According to him: “Your future as Abians is bright. I have since decided to quit politics in 2023 to give way for you all. If I don’t quit, there won’t be space for you. But I have to quit so that you can take over.”  Source The Arewa Youths Consultative Forum, AYCF, has stated that the North will not cede the presidency in 2023 to the South. According to Vanguard, the President of the AYCF, Shettima Yerima made this known in an interview on Tuesday. Yerima said it irritates the entire North for some southern politicians… June 22, 2020 In "News" •Atiku Abubakar ABUJA - A broad-based political alliance involving eminent leaders and chieftains of the opposition Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) across the six geopolitical zones is being put together with a two-pronged agenda, one of which is to neutralise the hold of former Vice President and presidential candidate of the… December 1, 2019 In "Politics" The Biafra Nations Youth League, BNYL, has tackled former Governor of Abia State, Orji Uzor Kalu over his recent boast that he can bring back Mazi Nnamdi Kanu, leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra, IPOB, to Nigeria. Recall that Senator Kalu had yesterday pleaded with President Muhammadu Buhari government… September 10, 2020 In "Politics"